verse_content.Word_by_word:
śreyān—greater; dravyamayāt—than the sacrifice of material possessions;
yajñāt—knowledge; jñāna-yajñaḥ—sacrifice in knowledge; parantapa—O
chastiser of the enemy; sarvam—all; karma—activities; akhilam—in totality;
pārtha—O son of Pṛthā; jñāne—in knowledge; parisamāpyate—ends in.
